cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on grammatical error correction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also describes the use of neural machine translation (NMT) models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper incorporates several enhancements to improve the performance of the NMT models, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Wikipedia revision histories as a source of training data, which could fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
